snippet.textDisplay: It’s strange — to love the thing that hurts you. But maybe it’s not the song that’s hurting me. Maybe it’s the truth I keep trying to avoid, finally finding a voice. And maybe healing doesn’t come all at once. Maybe it comes in verses and refrains — in the ache that reminds you you’re still alive. So I listen again. And again. And again. Because somehow, being broken by this song makes me feel whole...
snippet.textOriginal: It’s strange — to love the thing that hurts you. But maybe it’s not the song that’s hurting me. Maybe it’s the truth I keep trying to avoid, finally finding a voice.
